cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.AI, cs.NE 

The paper deals with deep learning for visual recognition, specifically in the context of multimedia applications. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel extension of residual learning for deep networks, which falls under the category of machine learning and neural networks, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. The paper also mentions large-scale content recognition, which could fall under cs.MM (Multimedia). Additionally, the paper discusses the integration of complex relations between closely coupled recognition tasks, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
